# picogame_bitfont - a tiny 8x8, 2-bit (4-shade, outlined/anti-aliased) bitmap font with game
# glyphs (codes 0..31 = arrows/hearts/sword/note/pipes; 32+ = ASCII). Renders a string to a
# picogame PAL8 Bitmap whose index 0 is transparent, so text reads cleanly OVER gameplay (the
# built-in dark outline gives contrast without a HUD box). Plain file on CIRCUITPY = easy to swap;
# if RAM is tight, fall back to picogame_font + terminalio instead.
#
# Font art derived from python-ugame/circuitpython-stage (MIT, (c) Radomir Dopieralski); repacked.
# (Ecosystem layer -> attribute in THIRD_PARTY.md; not the pristine picogame-libs bundle.)
#
#   import picogame_bitfont as bf
#   bmp, w, h = bf.render_text(pg, "SCORE 0")             # white text, dark outline, transparent bg
#   spr = pg.Sprite(bmp, x, y)                            # place anywhere; scale up via spr.scale
#   # symbols: bf.HEART, bf.ARROW_R ... e.g. bf.render_text(pg, "LIVES " + bf.HEART*3)

